            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "1. Having to `#include <pthread.h>` means all the \"portable\" C code is now tainted with OS-specific includes, making static analysis a lot harder.\r\n2. We don't actually need most of pthreads-win32, we only need mutexes, so making a small wrapper that exposes exactly what we need allows us to strictly limit the amount of system-dependent APIs we use. So no, this is not \"implement pthreads-win32\".",
            "created_at": "2018-07-19T19:21:33Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore/issues/1002#issuecomment-406386403",
            "id": 406386403,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/TokTok/c-toxcore/issues/1002",
            "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwNjM4NjQwMw==",
